                    |  Communications that we provide to you in electronic form may be provided in the following forms as determined by GFC: (a) via e-mail at the e-mail address you specify in your account on the Platform, (b) by access to a web site that we will designate in an e-mail notice we send to you at the time the information is available, (c) by access to a web site that will generally be designated in advance for such purpose, (d) by requesting you download a PDF file or (e) by displaying information to you on the Platform through text, graphic, pop-up window or otherwise.
                li.pb10.text-justify
                    u.font-weight-bold How to Withdraw Consent:    
                    |   You may withdraw your consent to receive Communications in electronic form but doing so will cause you to lose access to the Platform and any information contained in your account on the Platform. We may treat your provision of an invalid email address or the subsequent malfunction of a previously valid address as a withdrawal of your consent to receive electronic Communications. We will not impose any fee to process the withdrawal of your consent to receive electronic Communications. Any withdrawal of your consent to receive electronic Communications will be effective only after we have a reasonable period of time to process your withdrawal. To withdraw your consent, you must e-mail 
